Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_do_lec(25.10)                                        write_do_lec(25.10)

Name
       write_do_lec  -  Writes  out  the  dofile  for the Conformal(R) Logical
       Equivalence Checker tool

Syntax
       write_do_lec

       [-help]

       [-1801_golden <fileName>]

       [-1801_revised <fileName>]

       [-checkpoint <fileName>]

       [-cpf_golden <fileName>]

       [-cpf_revised <fileName>]

       [-cw_sim <simulationLanguage>]

       [-dft_constraint_file <fileName>]

       [-env_var <envVariables>]

       [-fastelab2gen]

       [-fastgen2fvmap]

       [-fastrtl2elab]

       [-golden_design {rtl|fv_map|<file>}]

       [-gzip_fv_json]

       [-log_file <fileName>]

       [-low_power_analysis]

       [-no_dft]

       [-no_exit]

       [-no_insert_iso_in_dof]

       [-no_lp]

       [-post_compare <fileName>]

       [-post_read_power_intent <fileName>]

       [-pre_compare <fileName>]

       [-pre_exit <fileName>]

       [-pre_read <fileName>]

       [-pre_read_design <fileName>]

       [-pre_read_power_intent <fileName>]

       [-pre_verification_information <fileName>]

       [-revised_design {fv_map|<file>}]

       [-rtl_revised]

       [-sim_lib <simulationLibrary>]

       [-sim_plus_liberty]

       [-smart]

       [-tmp_dir <directoryName>]

       [-top <designName>]

       [-verbose]

       [-write_session <fileName>]

       [-hier  | -flat ] [<output_filename> | >]

       Writes out the dofile for the Conformal(R) Logical Equivalence  Checker
       tool.

       For   formal   verification  of  the  Innovus-generated  netlists,  the
       write_do_lec command  generates,  within  Innovus,  the  Conformal  LEC
       scripts (such as dofile). These scripts are used for equivalence check-
       ing.  You  can generate a flat or a hierarchical comparison script. The
       dofile written out by this command  contains  standard  Conformal  flow
       commands  and  you  will  need to add the DFT constraints if netlist is
       scan inserted.

       The write_do_lec command creates a verification directory, if does  not
       already  exist, in which the name mapping information file will be cre-
       ated. The name mapping file will usually contain the  mapping  informa-
       tion  of MBIT flops against its split/single bit candidate. By default,
       the name of this verification directory  is  fv/invs/%s.  You  can  use
       write_lec_directory_naming_style to change the directory name.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each write_do_lec parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man write_do_lec

       -1801_golden <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the golden (original) 1801 file.  This op-
              tion only applies to the IEEE-1801 flow.

       -1801_revised <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the revised 1801 file that corresponds  to
              the  current  state  of the design.  This option only applies to
              the IEEE-1801 flow.

       -checkpoint <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the checkpoint file to generate.

       -cpf_golden <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the golden (original) file.

              If omitted, the file will be inferred from the cpf_files  design
              attribute.

              This option only applies to the CPF flow.

       -cpf_revised <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the revised CPF file.

              If  you omit this option, the file specified for the -cpf_golden
              option will be used.

              If you expect name changes in the CPF design objects,  you  must
              generate  this  file  using the write_power_intent -cpf command.
              This option only applies to the CPF flow.

       -cw_sim <simulationLanguage>
              Specifies the language of the simulation models that the Confor-
              mal Logical Equivalence Checker should use to infer the ChipWare
              components.

              You can specify any of the following values:

              {V1995|V2001|SV|VHDL1987|VHDL1993}

              Default: Language specified in the read_hdl command.

       -dft_constraint_file <fileName>
              Sources DFT constraints from the specified file before executing
              the compare command.

       -env_var <envVariables>
              Specifies the names and values of UNIX environment variables  to
              be used for directory and file names in the dofile.

       -fastrtl2elab
              Generates  an  abbreviated LEC dofile for quick diagnosis of RTL
              vs elaborated.

       -fastelab2gen
              Generates an abbreviated LEC dofile for quick diagnosis of elab-
              orated vs generic.

       -fastgen2fvmap
              Generates an abbreviated  LEC  dofile  for  quick  diagnosis  of
              generic vs fv_map.

       <output_filename>
              Redirects all the output to the specified file.

       -flat  Performs a flattened Conformal LEC comparison.

       -golden_design {rtl|fv_map|<file>}
              Specifies  the  golden design to compare to. You can specify the
              following values:

              * rtl: write_do_lec will access the  hdl_filelist  attribute  to
                use the same set of files that were read into Innovus.

              * fv_map:  write_do_lec will use the netlist automatically writ-
                ten by Innovus during mapping (syn_map).

              * <file>: Specifies the UNIX path to an alternative  golden  de-
                sign.

              If  the  file  was loaded into Innovus (using either read_hdl or
              read_netlist), the tool knows the language format of  the  file.
              Otherwise,  the tool assumes that the format of the file is Ver-
              ilog-1995.

              Default: rtl

       -gzip_fv_json
              Specifies to compress the implementation information file.

              This option is available with Conformal 19.10-s300 or newer ver-
              sions.

       -hier  Specifies whether to do hierarchical LEC comparison or not.

       -log_file <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the Conformal LEC logfile.

       -low_power_analysis
              Specifies to add the Conformal Low Power commands to compare the
              power domains between the golden and revised designs. Power  in-
              tent must be present.

       -no_dft
              Prevents that DFT constraints are written to the dofile.

       -no_exit
              Does not add the exit command to the end of the dofile.

       -no_insert_iso_in_dof
              Prevents  that  the -insert_isolation option is added to the LEC
              commit power intent commands for the golden and  revised  design
              in the generated dofile.

              Use this option when you write out a dofile before the power in-
              tent  is committed in Innovus (before using the commit_power_in-
              tent command).

       -no_lp Prevents verification of power intent information.

       -post_compare <fileName>
              Specifies a dofile to be sourced from the LEC dofile just  after
              the comparison.

       -post_read_power_intent <fileName>
              Specifies  a dofile to be sourced from the LEC dofile just after
              read_power_intent.

       -pre_compare <fileName>
              Specifies an extra dofile that must  be  sourced  from  the  LEC
              dofile  before the LEC set system mode lec or write hier_compare
              dofile command.

       -pre_exit <fileName>
              Specifies an extra dofile that must  be  sourced  from  the  LEC
              dofile before the LEC exit command.

       -pre_read <fileName>
              Specifies  an  extra  dofile  that  must be sourced from the LEC
              dofile before the library and design are read.

       -pre_read_design <fileName>
              Specifies a dofile to be sourced from the LEC dofile just before
              reading the design.

       -pre_read_power_intent <fileName>
              Specifies a dofile to be sourced from the LEC dofile just before
              read_power_intent.

       -pre_verification_information <fileName>
              Specifies a dofile to be sourced from the LEC dofile just before
              setting the verification information.

       -revised_design {fv_map|<file>}
              Specifies the revised design to compare to  the  golden  design.
              You can specify the following values:

              * fv_map:  write_do_lec will use the netlist automatically writ-
                ten by Innovus during mapping (syn_map).

              * <file>: Specifies the UNIX path to the revised design.

       -rtl_revised
              Specifies that the revised design is DFT inserted back-annotated
              RTL.

       -sim_lib <simulationLibrary>
              Specifies the simulation library in Verilog 1995.

       -sim_plus_liberty
              Specifies that the simulation library is an addition to the syn-
              thesis library.

       -smart Enables advanced SMART Lec capabilities.

              Requires a Conformal SMARTLec license.

       -tmp_dir <directoryName>
              Specifies the name of the directory to which the generated files
              must be written.

       -top <designName>
              Specifies the name of the top-level design in Innovus.

       -verbose
              Generates a dofile with verbose reporting.

       -write_session <fileName>
              Specifies the filename to save the LEC session.

Examples
              * The following command will source the extra_settigs.do  dofile
                before the compare command in the sample.do file.

                write_do_lec -revised revised.v -pre_compare extra_settings.do
                > sample.do

              * The  following  command  generates a dofile that will point to
                the System Verilog simulation models of  all  ChipWare  compo-
                nents used in the design.

                write_do_lec  -revised_design  ../netlist/top_nl.v -cw_sim sv\
                     -log_file cw_sim_sv.log > cw_sim.sv_lec.do

